line_1: With shelving rocks and trees o'erhung,
line_2: And ravens pester all day long;

line_1: Deep superstition's night the skies o'erhung,
line_2: Beneath whose baleful dews the poppy sprung.

line_1: Beneath a rock with venturous trees o'erhung,
line_2: That seem by some enchantment to have sprang,
